# DrishtiSeva web — Netlify routing rules
#
# 1) Proxy /api/* and /uploads/* to the Railway API.
#    The bundle calls relative paths (no VITE_API_BASE was set at build),
#    so Netlify forwards them to the API and the auth cookie round-trips
#    same-origin (no SameSite=None gymnastics needed).
#
#    🚨 BEFORE FIRST DEPLOY: replace REPLACE-WITH-RAILWAY-URL with the
#    actual Railway public domain (e.g. drishtiseva-production.up.railway.app).
#    Find it in your Railway dashboard → service → Settings → Networking →
#    Public Domain, or run `railway status` locally.
#
/api/*       https://REPLACE-WITH-RAILWAY-URL/api/:splat       200
/uploads/*   https://REPLACE-WITH-RAILWAY-URL/uploads/:splat   200

# 2) SPA fallback — every other path serves index.html so React Router /
#    the in-memory view switcher in App.tsx handles deep links on refresh.
/*           /index.html                                       200
